text: Milton Palacios (died 7 February 2000) was a former football player and manager. ==Club career== Palacios played for UES for a few seasons. ==Managerial career== Palacios, coached various teams in panama including Plaza Amador, Panamá Viejo FC and San Francisco FC. he also coached in his native country in particular for the club he played for UES. ==References== ==External links== * - Panama America Category:2000 deaths Category:Salvadoran footballers Category:Salvadoran football managers Category:Liga Panameña de Fútbol managers Category:Association footballers not categorized by position Category:Year of birth missing
title: Milton Palacios (football manager)
